Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Quarter @lime{1}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Reduce heat under pan to low; stir in @sweet soy glaze{8%tablespoon} and 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Cook, turning chicken occasionally, until sauce has slightly thickened and chicken is evenly coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

While chicken cooks, in a medium microwave-safe bowl, combine broccoli, scallion whites, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Cover with #plastic wrap{}; poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave until tender, ~{1 1/2-3%minutes}. Drain.

> No microwave? No problem! Boil broccoli in a pot of salted water until tender, ~{2-4%minutes}. Drain.

Toss broccoli with as many @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Season with @salt{}.

Massage @microwavable rice{1} in package to separate grains; partially open package. Microwave for ~{90%seconds}. Carefully open package; stir in @cashews{1%ounce}, @butter{1%TBSP}, juice from one lime wedge, and a pinch of @salt{} (2 TBSP butter and juice from two wedges for 4).

In a small #bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and juice from one lime wedge (juice from two wedges for 4 servings).

Divide rice between bowls and top with saucy chicken and broccoli in separate sections. Drizzle everything with spicy mayo. Top with scallion greens and @crispy fried onions{1}. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.